// Intent: a concrete "author a doc" instruction must drive the agent to actually
// CALL the write_file tool (not just describe a PRD), finish cleanly, and mention
// the PRD in its final reply. We deliberately do NOT assert an exact path/title:
// `CalledToolWith` is a JSON subset match on VALUE equality, so a `path` like
// "prd/" would never match the model's real exact path string. Asserting "called
// write_file at least once + no error + talks about a PRD" keeps this robust to
// reasonable model variation while still exercising the tool-using loop.
(
  name: "create-prd-calls-write-file",
  instruction: "Create a PRD for a dark-mode toggle setting and save it under prd/. The PRD should cover the problem, the proposed toggle behavior, and a short success metric.",
  expect: [
    CalledTool(tool: "write_file"),
    ToolCallCount(tool: Some("write_file"), min: Some(1)),
    NoError,
    FinalTextContains(text: "prd", case_insensitive: true),
  ],
)
